Modifications in this fork include:
- FinClaw OSS integration uses a unified FinDataHub A-share data layer
- Three new A-stock specific analyst agents (Policy, Hot Money, Lockup)
- A-stock trading constraints (T+1, price limits, lot sizes) in Trader and PM
- Chinese language output support
- CSI 300 benchmark for alpha calculation (replacing SPY)
- Various prompt and pipeline adaptations for A-share market specifics

See CHANGES_FROM_UPSTREAM.md for the full list of modifications.

FinClaw OSS integration notes:
- Bundled as a FinClaw capability under capabilities/tradingagents_astock
- Uses FinClaw/FinDataHub as the default data service when launched by FinClaw
- Provides a self-contained HTML report renderer without BettaFish ReportEngine
